    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>My goodness. I&#8217;m in the UK. I&#8217;ve followed this blog for a while, and listening to the podcast while I cook or do housework is a ritual for me. In fact about half an hour ago, I finished binge-listening four episodes. Then I read this, and gasped aloud. I have two children, and I came out to myself when I was 40. I&#8217;m now in a beautiful relationship with a woman which fulfils me completely. I&#8217;m still friends with my ex-husband and we co-parent as you do. I can&#8217;t explain to myself how it took so long to realise what is now as plain to me as the nose on my face, and I know the confusion of trying to narrativise that. I also know that I still look everywhere for similar stories to make mine feel less odd and more familiar. I&#8217;m delighted that you of all people just gave me one! Good luck on your journey, it&#8217;s really the best ever and can be completely joyful.</p>
