    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>When a new post from Orangette popped up in my blog reader, I thought, &#8220;Oh thank God.&#8221; Even before reading this, I&#8217;ve was thinking that your words have sustained me through some very difficult times.  I found your writing during my divorce from a man who realized that he could not be married to a woman anymore.  Your honesty and wonder at the world around you reminded me that part of being a human being was the hard stuff, too. I learned that the rhythms of the kitchen and the good gifts of everyday life could keep me grounded and centered. And sane. </p>
