    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I started reading Orangette when I was pregnant with my daughter in 2012. I made the chocolate cherry granola bars and the Thai beef stir fry. I read about your delivery to help prepare for mine. I enjoyed reading about your memories of Oklahoma City because that&#8217;s where I lived at the time. At the beginning of this year, I read A Homemade Life as I sat in a nursing home with my mother, a lesbian who came out at 40 while married to my father. This summer, when my dying mother&#8217;s cancer allowed her to have an appetite, I often thought of the grotto eggs as I made my mom turkey burgers, quiche, sweet corn, and artichokes with Hellman&#8217;s. I read about your father&#8217;s death to help prepare for my mother&#8217;s, and when she died last month, I wasn&#8217;t afraid. I dont know the rules for reaching out to a favorite blogger, but I have long enjoyed coming here to read about the best bad ideas.</p>
    </div>

