    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly,  also whom I don&#8217;t know ;), I&#8217;ve been thinking of you lately and missing your blog. Thank you SO much for being so vulnerable and sharing all of this with us! Your words are beautiful and powerful and they are inspiring me to sit down and continue writing. I&#8217;ve been working on a book for a full year now and sometimes I lose sight of why, of what the point is. Thank you for reminding me that stories and heartfelt words are some of the most important gifts we can give people. This story of yours was a gift. I know you might not see it that way now, but some day I hope you do. Wishing you strength and hope! xo</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59521' data-commentid="59521" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59521" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Christy Krumm Richard" aria-label='Reply to Christy Krumm Richard'>Reply</a>    </div>
