    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Weeping my makeup right off on this rainy NYC day. I have looked up to you from almost the very beginning of this blog and have been constantly inspired by your courage. Thank you for once again opening your heart to us all. My brother and I come from a family that looks a lot like yours in many ways- just like June, we grew up in our parents&#8217; restaurant where our father was involved most on premise, and our father came out to us when we were still young and they were divorced. They have remained very best friends and both my brother and I feel that we have more rather than less. I always say to friends who are contemplating divorce or major life changes that the most important influence our parents had on us was fighting for their own happiness.  Sending you, and Brendan, and June all my love.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
