    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Dear Molly,<br />
I started reading your blog when you started writing it. When you started writing about Brandon, and the way that you loved each other, it made me sad for myself, and ultimately brave enough, after 7 years of deep unhappiness, to leave my husband at age 44.  Ironically, like you, it took me ending up in an emergency room after not sleeping for 3 days to give me the final push.  Which took so  long mostly because I was devastated about the impact it would have on my then 9 year old daughter.  What I quickly learned is that I should have left years before the unhappiness got to that point when I started feeling differently about the person I was married to &#8211; when my daughter was much, much  younger &#8211; about June&#8217;s age.  I think it would have been better for all of us.  But after a very rough few years, I am now so happy, I am happily remarried and had another beautiful daughter 3 1/2 years ago.  It&#8217;s been really, really hard at times.  But it is also so much better.  I have always wanted to write you to thank  you for making me brave.  Now seems like the time.  You are so, so brave.  And so full of grace.  I think this may be the most beautiful thing you have ever written.  And that&#8217;s saying something.  Blessings to you.</p>
    </div>

