    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>&#8220;Having a baby, having her, softened me. It broke me a little. It gave me first-hand knowledge of the fullness of joy and the emptiness of clinical depression. It made me appreciate my body, and femaleness, in a new way. It committed me to becoming the kind of person I want June to know and remember and be proud of. It committed me to being a person I want to parent her. It made me brave.&#8221;<br />
This. This is motherhood. Especially motherhood of daughters. We cannot expect them to be strong and honest women if we are not the same. Honestly, that is why I quilt as much as I write. This is me. And to be a great mother I need to be me. You had a difficult move to make for that to happen for you, but Brava for doing so.</p>
    </div>

