    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly,<br />
We met briefly when you came to Sitka and you signed my copy of  &#8220;A Homemade Life&#8221;. I hadn&#8217;t actually read the book before your presentation at the library but I was in for a real inspirational treat. I found myself in your writing and feel very grateful to you for that. You opened a few windows in my soul that felt stuck shut in terms of grief, writing, and even enjoying the creation of food. Today, you&#8217;ve done that again. It&#8217;s always so comforting to find more folks who are understanding their sexuality in a new way like I have been. Thank you for continuing to share yourself with us so beautifully. I am honored to be able to witness your journey. *Cyber Hugs*</p>
