      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.thedomesticfront.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Caitlin</a></cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59630"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-11-30T19:48:21-05:00">Wednesday, November 30, 2016 at 7:48 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I am constantly amazed by your willingness to be your most vulnerable self in public &#8211; I think it does lend a power to your writing that others don&#8217;t have.  That said, I&#8217;m sorry to hear about the end of your marriage as you knew it &#8211; motherhood is a particularly profound change, and some institutions and relationships that fit us perfectly at some point in our earlier life may not be able to change with us.  This whole figuring out your life shit is hard.  But you seem to be doing it with a great deal of grace, if not painlessly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59630' data-commentid="59630" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59630" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Caitlin" aria-label='Reply to Caitlin'>Reply</a>    </div>
