    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>What beautiful and courageous writing. Thank you for this post &#8211; and thank you for the whole site. I started reading your blog about two years ago when I was halfway through college, and it&#8217;s always been my leading favorite &#8211; for your recipes, your writing, your sense of style and sense of self.<br />
My parents divorced when I was about June&#8217;s age, after over ten years of marriage.  I can&#8217;t comprehend what divorce is like from a mother&#8217;s perspective (and certainly it&#8217;s different for every family &#8212; like Tolstoy says!) but for me, I always thought of my mom and dad as two different, friendly teams. My dad&#8217;s team grew to include a step-mom and two new half-brothers, and my mom&#8217;s team remained me, my mom, and my brother. My two families, two households, could coexist and cheer the other on; I wouldn&#8217;t have had it any other way.<br />
So anyway, this is just to say that I&#8217;m sure there&#8217;s still so much joy for you and June ahead. xoxo. Hope to read more soon</p>
    </div>

