      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59685"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-11-30T23:35:58-05:00">Wednesday, November 30, 2016 at 11:35 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly,<br />
I just had to reach out and tell you that you are so brave. Thank you for being vulnerable. June is going to be so proud that you are her mother when she is an adult. I hope my daughter ( my baby of 20!) will be the same kind of amazing woman that you are. I believe she is gaining a lot from the women she sees around her-modeling the authenticity of your generation. I send positive thoughts to you, Brandon, and sweet June.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59685' data-commentid="59685" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59685" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Suzanne Christman" aria-label='Reply to Suzanne Christman'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-59687" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Ann Callahan</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59687"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-11-30T23:58:38-05:00">Wednesday, November 30, 2016 at 11:58 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>There&#8217;s not really anything unique I can say, but I feel compelled to respond. You have been an inspiration to me over several years and in many ways. I have experienced divorce and I agree, it does feel like some kind of death or failure. And I think it is those things. But the death is more like the death of my larkspur flowers, which re-seed themselves, joyfully, every year. And the failure can be, trite as it may sound, the path to success. All those glimmers of what the future can hold are there for you and Brandon and June. More so than at any time in history. Your honesty will benefit yourself- but it will also benefit so many others in  ripples that will travel far. It helps me, in times of stress, just to know that other people care. If it helps you, know that I am among the many who care about you and your family.  PS- Hope you can squeeze in another post before the end of the year. I&#8217;m parched for your musings!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59687' data-commentid="59687" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59687" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Ann Callahan" aria-label='Reply to Ann Callahan'>Reply</a>    </div>
