    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#8217;ve come back to read this several times since yesterday. I am so astounded by your bravery &#8211; not only in realizing this about yourself, and opening up to it, but in sharing it here, with us. You invited the world into your life and your marriage with your blog and your two wonderful books. I&#8217;ve always been amazed at the honesty in Delancey &#8211; written after the first-blush love of your early relationship, when cracks were showing and mending. I&#8217;m at that point in my own marriage, and the uncertainty is terrifying. Your writing helps.<br />
I (and I&#8217;m sure many others) felt a certain… ownership isn&#8217;t the right word, but I guess an investment in your relationship. We&#8217;d seen it grow from the beginning. I&#8217;m sure you&#8217;re aware of that. I can&#8217;t imagine how it compounded your fear when you decided to separate. But the truth is, you don&#8217;t owe us anything. We are lucky that you chose to give us a window into your life, and we&#8217;re lucky that you trust us enough to keep it open. I am filled with admiration for you &#8211; that you did the best thing for yourself and June and Brandon by living honestly. I&#8217;m so sorry that you are going through so much pain, but thank you for writing about it so beautifully. I think you all are going to be ok.</p>
    </div>

