      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59755"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-01T13:27:07-05:00">Thursday, December 1, 2016 at 1:27 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I met you at a book signing several years ago, as I was approaching the end of my undergrad years in New York. I told you that one of the things that I liked best about your writing was the sense that it gave me that even though I was still figuring myself and my future out, everything would be okay. And you smiled and laughed and you said to me, &#8220;That&#8217;s because it will be okay!&#8221; </p>
<p>I&#8217;m so honored &#8211; as I know everyone here is honored &#8211; that you let us into your life in this way, and that you write with such hopeful conviction that it will all be okay. </p>
<p>Sending you the warmest wishes from New York.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59755' data-commentid="59755" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59755" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Maria" aria-label='Reply to Maria'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-59756" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Liz Wharton</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59756"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-01T13:41:28-05:00">Thursday, December 1, 2016 at 1:41 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>You just articulated thoughts I had nearly 35 years ago. I, too, was married with 2 beautiful sons busy in life and in our business. And for me, also, something shifted and I woke up, literally, to the fact that I was not happy with this man I&#8217;d known some 15 years. In fact, it came to me that all of the things I loved had to do with softness, lushness, deep intimacy of heart and mind.<br />
Now, 30 years into my marriage to Barb, my love and the woman who helped raise two fine men who have beautiful children of their own to love&#8230; now, as I read your thoughts, I remembered that anguish and confusion, the excitement and hesitancy and finally the validation of the truth of who I was &#8211; who I am &#8211; and triumph.<br />
So, my sister, I am grateful for the memories. Be true to yourself.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59756' data-commentid="59756" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59756" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Liz Wharton" aria-label='Reply to Liz Wharton'>Reply</a>    </div>
