    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>You lionheart. Way to take life by the horns, and to take a great risk.  And to be vulnerable here. It makes you even more dear to your readers. We, your friends, are with you as you take baby steps forward, and that includes daughters of divorced parents like myself, who see that it&#8217;s good for moms and dads to teach their kids to value authenticity.  I&#8217;m inspired enough by your heroic act (not precisely knowing what the future will bring) I just might feel courageous enough to do something drastic this Christmas.  A thing that I fear, but that I believe needs doing.  Deep breath.</p>
<p>PS I had a weird stomach for three days (either a food aversion or maybe the stomach flu?) and felt the need to be cautious about my intake in case it was the first, so for the first part of this week, I survived on Charlie Brigham Soup.  I need to refine my technique to be sure it isn&#8217;t too salty, but still, it got me through a rough patch. Grateful for that go-to. You&#8217;re a gift, and not just in the recipe-source category.</p>
    </div>

