    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Thank you for this post, and for all of them. I took a Food Anthropology class at the University of Washington in the fall of 2008&#8211;the first college course I had ever taken&#8211;and you gave a presentation to us about writing a blog. I did not even know what a blog was before this day. You inspired me so much that I eagerly bookmarked your site and I have been reading every post ever since. Yours was the first food blog I ever read and the one that I always will continue to read. Thank you for sharing everything that you do. It means a lot.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59809' data-commentid="59809" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59809" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Merek" aria-label='Reply to Merek'>Reply</a>    </div>
