    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have read your blog for  some years and loved so many things about it. I love this post and I am so happy for you that you have found your way to authenticity, that you  are creating a new way of being family with yours, and that your community has been so supportive! I came out a few years ago at age 50,  and have worked with my ex to create a new kind of family. It isn&#8217;t easy, especially in my cohort, but I think it is very important work which offers that possibility to others, to show that the ending of a marriage doesn&#8217;t have to be ugly and disastrous in every case.   For me it has been a pretty lonely journey, and I have not yet found love. But I would not trade the freedom of authenticity and honesty, of being true to myself, and ultimately I think that this is offers freedom to both my children and my former spouse. Blessings to you and yours!</p>
    </div>

