    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I have been listening to you on Spilled Milk and reading this blog for a long time now, and although I have never commented I am a true fan of your work. I am blown away at the honesty of your post and how brave it was to share this part of yourself. I want to let you know that as the child of divorced parents, divorce can be done well. You can show love and respect and your child will understand and see that not all relationships end because there is no love there. I am in my 30s now, and have so much admiration for the love and respect my parents showed each other during what was a very challenging time for them. It pulls at my heart to hear that June is as lucky as I was. Thank you for sharing and I hope that you are able to keep on sharing with this community- it is a beautiful and inspiring gift.</p>
