    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>You are brave and strong and true. I admire the shit out of you. When I came out at 32, married to a man, mother of two young boys, I felt like a mess and a failure. But I knew my truth and could not contain it. It took my oldest friend telling me that I was brave to help me see that I was indeed brave. To write like you did in this post, so honestly and clearly, is the embodiment of bravery.</p>
