    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Thank you so much for being exactly as you are, and for writing so honestly from that place. The timing is uncanny &#8211; I have a pork roast in the oven and wine chilling for our friends Heather and Kelly. They raised their children together while their husbands went off to work &#8211; and then, lo, seemingly out of the blue, they realized that they were profoundly in love with each other. There was initial tumult, but now, several years later, all has righted in their world. Their kids are great, their ex-husbands are happy, and THEY are happy. As are my partner and I. Which is to say&#8230; while I grieve for the part of you that is also grieving, I celebrate you exactly as you are, and exactly as you continue to evolve to be. Thank you for being here!</p>
