    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I&#8217;ve never commented before (long-time reader of the blog, books, etc, and a fellow Seattleite).  However, your post about post-partum depression, and particularly that you wished you hadn&#8217;t waited so long before getting help, led me to seek a therapist when my daughter was 4 weeks old.  I felt like everything about me was &#8220;wrong&#8221; for not feeling what I &#8220;should&#8221; have been feeling, but your honesty about your experience, particularly when I considered you to be so amazing and put-together, really was the factor that led me to seek therapy (and now to have a lovely, positive relationship with my 3 1/2 and 1 1/2 year old).  This present post is just as honest and vital.  I have not had the same feelings and so I cannot relate in the same way that I did to post-partum.  However, I think you are very brave for speaking your lived experience and I know that there are many people who are drawing validation, power &amp; action from your experience right now. Thank you for sharing.  Xo</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
