    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://tangerinedrawings.com/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Frances</a></cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59901"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-04T09:18:21-05:00">Sunday, December 4, 2016 at 9:18 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>This was beautifully written. Thank-you. I have been thinking about it all weekend.</p>
<p>Like many people here, I have been reading your words for years, online and in book form, and cooking from your recipes. I identified with your love for Paris, and knew what it felt like to lose a father. Now, this too. </p>
<p>I didn&#8217;t know I was not-straight until a friend of mine casually corrected an assumption of mine and told me she was bi. It sparked a long chain of thoughts that ended in &#8220;me too.&#8221; She turned on a light in a room I didn&#8217;t know I had. It didn&#8217;t feel like I had been suppressing something &#8211; I just didn&#8217;t know. It is still scary &#8211; I have moments of doubt. I am sometimes cross with myself for not knowing sooner (I&#8217;m 29 and feel like I have to start over as a teenager again). I am trying to live in that in-between space, as you expressed:</p>
<p>&#8220;I don’t know what word to call myself – gay, lesbian, bi, queer – and I don’t really care.&#8221; Even without a label, I feel more like myself than I ever did before.</p>
<p>All this to say: I am grateful for you sharing your own story, however vulnerable it makes you feel. It is so valuable to be able to say, &#8220;me too.&#8221; There may be someone else reading this who will also have a lightbulb moment, who will feel less alone, thanks to you.</p>
<p>P.S. You were featured on Things I Read That I Loved (Autostraddle), another of my favourite internet places.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59901' data-commentid="59901" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59901" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Frances" aria-label='Reply to Frances'>Reply</a>    </div>
