    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I too have been reading your blog for a long time&#8230;. Before Brandon, before June and I just wanted to say that though I seldom comment I do think about you a lot! I introduced my MIL to your blog and it has been one of those things that help us connect, &#8220;Did you see Molly&#8217;s latest post?!&#8221; Or, &#8220;Did you try this recipe of Molly&#8217;s?!&#8221; People always ask, &#8220;Who is Molly?&#8221; Expecting that it is some long, lost friend they have never met and not a food blogger in Seattle! Well I guess they are right&#8230;. We do talk and think about you as if you are our friend. We share your joys and triumphs as well as your sorrows and losses because you let us. Thank you for being so brave and true to yourself! I am so proud of you! xo</p>
