    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I only read this blog post today, but I&#8217;d had the feeling for some time that you had some big news to share with us. I knew you&#8217;d share when you were good and ready, because it felt like it was something that was none of anybody else&#8217;s business.  I vaguely thought it would involve one of those stressful &#8220;life changes&#8221;  (years ago they included moving, changing jobs, change in marital status, the addition or loss of a close family member, among other things), but I wasn&#8217;t quite expecting this to be your big news! Honestly, I thought it would be be  the news of a new restaurant, new home, or new child. As so many others have said, I wish you nothing but the best, and are in awe of your bravery and honesty.</p>
<p>Good thoughts sent to you here in Ballard, to Brandon on Capitol Hill, and to June at both. Plus moms and pets, wherever they may be.</p>
    </div>

