    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#8217;ve been reading since almost the very beginning. It&#8217;s hard to believe how much time has gone by. My life has changed drastically over the years as well. This isn&#8217;t the first time your words have brought tears to my eyes and I&#8217;m sure it won&#8217;t be the last&#8230; and I mean that in the best possible way. 🙂 I&#8217;ve loved your writing since the day I first stumbled across Orangette. I can still picture the candied orange peels in your banner. I think maybe they were dipped in chocolate? I&#8217;m rambling, What I really want to say is, thank you for sharing your beautiful, heartbreaking, joyful and brave story. I have one too (we all do), but I&#8217;m still learning how to tell it. I&#8217;m in awe of your honesty, of your voice. Wishing you and yours peace, love and joy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59971' data-commentid="59971" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59971" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jody" aria-label='Reply to Jody'>Reply</a>    </div>
