      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59977"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-06T11:47:06-05:00">Tuesday, December 6, 2016 at 11:47 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Here&#8217;s to you, Molly, in every bit of your beautiful, vulnerable, brave, changing glory.  May we all be willing to embrace the changes that come our way in life.  Go, girl!  xoxoxo</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59977' data-commentid="59977" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59977" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jamie" aria-label='Reply to Jamie'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-59978" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Katie</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59978"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-06T11:54:32-05:00">Tuesday, December 6, 2016 at 11:54 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have been following this site  for years- since before I was married, before I became a mother to my son and my now 9 month old daughter.  In a lot of ways I feel like I have grown into adulthood with you, although I have never commented.  Thank you for sharing so much of yourself with the world in such a beautiful way.  Vulnerability and honesty are powerful things.  I wish all the best for you, Brandon, and June as your life takes on a new shape together.  Keep exploring, keep discovering, and keep writing!!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59978' data-commentid="59978" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59978" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Katie" aria-label='Reply to Katie'>Reply</a>    </div>
