  <li id="comment-59980" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Puck</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59980"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-06T13:01:33-05:00">Tuesday, December 6, 2016 at 1:01 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I&#8217;ve read your blog for years but never cried reading it before. You are very brave to write like this. I&#8217;ve been through the same experience, but the other way around. I left my girlfriend of twelve years because I realised I was straight, and am now happily married. My girlfriend and I are best friends and I am godmother to her little girl. The pain lingers but you can heal and be happier on the other side. I wish you all the best. You are not alone &#8211; more people than you think have been through such a shift. x</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59980' data-commentid="59980" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59980" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Puck" aria-label='Reply to Puck'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-59981" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
