      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59985"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-06T15:05:13-05:00">Tuesday, December 6, 2016 at 3:05 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Thank you for your courage in sharing your story. It sounds like you are surrounded by safe people and places, and that is a gift. Please know that you are wrapped in love and prayers for peace in the midst of all the changes.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59985' data-commentid="59985" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59985" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Melanie G" aria-label='Reply to Melanie G'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-59986" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Keri</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-59986"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-06T16:07:16-05:00">Tuesday, December 6, 2016 at 4:07 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have been reading your blog almost since it began, and the reason for my loyalty, aside from the wonderful recipes, is your ability to be vulnerable and honest and true to yourself. Thank you for that. I&#8217;ll keep coming back to read more of your story. I won&#8217;t belabour the sentiments written so well above, except to say two things. The first is that I&#8217;m a child of divorced parents who didn&#8217;t like one another, and the fact that you and Brandon will remain amicable parents of your wonderful daughter is an enormous gift to her. The second is that the way you each invite love into your life as you go forward will be a further gift to June. She&#8217;ll see embodied all the ways that love is joyful and confusing and intellectually stimulating and she&#8217;ll see that love belongs to the two people who share it, no matter their gender or background or origins.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-59986' data-commentid="59986" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-59986" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Keri" aria-label='Reply to Keri'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
