  <li id="comment-60000" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">MILA</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60000"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-06T22:53:59-05:00">Tuesday, December 6, 2016 at 10:53 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I came here to poke around for some Christmas recipe ideas and was stunned when your I read your first few, beautifully honest and naked paragraphs. Then I read on and felt such awe at your bravery,  your self-awareness, and your deep compassion for your family. June will be fine. Your family will change and grow and it will become richer, too. My parents got divorced when I was five and it was hard at the time. But my mom eventually found a female partner who has brought her great joy and comfort and our family is full and loving. I&#8217;m thirty now and I&#8217;m happy that she found her path and found herself in ways that she surely wouldn&#8217;t have imagined when I was born. Good luck to you and thank you for your powerful writing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60000' data-commentid="60000" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60000" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to MILA" aria-label='Reply to MILA'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-60007" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Cat</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60007"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-07T11:15:52-05:00">Wednesday, December 7, 2016 at 11:15 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I confess I feel sad for you and Brandon. Having been through a divorce of my own, I know the particular devastation that a radical life change like that brings<br />
to your world, even when the divorce is for the best of reasons. I wish you nothing but the best. I re-read &#8216;A homemade life&#8217; again this week, and as always I enjoy your voice and clarity. Ive been a faithful reader since 2012. I&#8217;ll still be a faithful reader, and I hope you continue to share your life.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60007' data-commentid="60007" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60007" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Cat" aria-label='Reply to Cat'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-60018" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">andrea</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60018"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-07T20:56:09-05:00">Wednesday, December 7, 2016 at 8:56 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Your post is raw and beautiful, as are so many of the replies. I am glad you are supported and loved both in real life and virtually. We only get one go-round (at least I believe that)&#8230;all we can do is live it as best and as truthfully as we can.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60018' data-commentid="60018" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60018" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to andrea" aria-label='Reply to andrea'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-60020" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Erin</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60020"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-07T22:33:50-05:00">Wednesday, December 7, 2016 at 10:33 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I have read this post 4 or 5 times and it takes my breath away. Your bravery, your ability to write your story publically, your ability to come out while not knowing yet what that means. My partner and I both come from divorce (his split when he was 6, and mine when i was 25)  and his ability to grow and love his stepfamilies taught me how to love mine. Mostly, I love that I finally get more family that loves each other more openly. June will benefit from every part of what you and Brandon are embarking on even if it sometimes hurts.<br />
 Finally, I leave you with this song from one of my favorite bands, Hop Along, because I feel like we like similar music, and the theme applies <a href="https://youtu.be/AhtVc8obuSg" rel="nofollow ugc">https://youtu.be/AhtVc8obuSg</a></p>
<p>Molly you are phenomenal.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60020' data-commentid="60020" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60020" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Erin" aria-label='Reply to Erin'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-60022" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Aarthi</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60022"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-08T00:14:53-05:00">Thursday, December 8, 2016 at 12:14 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>So brave Molly and beautiful writing.  My best wishes to you and your lovely family</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60022' data-commentid="60022" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60022" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Aarthi" aria-label='Reply to Aarthi'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-60025" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://forcedbloom.wordpress.com/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Linda Friday</a></cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60025"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-08T04:03:54-05:00">Thursday, December 8, 2016 at 4:03 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Ah, Molly: I can only echo what everyone else has said&#8211;this family of (mostly) strangers who think of you as one of their own. You and Brandon are both brave pathfinders and I have no doubt that you will blaze new trails for a new normal. June will flourish because she has superlative parents. Your writing always takes my breath away, but today my heart stopped.  I am certain this journey will not be without twists and turns, but I am also certain of your ability to navigate it all with grit and grace. I hope your life continues to unfold in wild and wondrous ways. Thank you for trusting us. XOX</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60025' data-commentid="60025" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60025" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Linda Friday" aria-label='Reply to Linda Friday'>Reply</a>    </div>
