      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60040"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-08T13:55:03-05:00">Thursday, December 8, 2016 at 1:55 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#8217;ve had this post pulled up in my browser for several days and but didn&#8217;t have a chance to read it until yesterday and instantly regretted taking so long to finally get to it. Today, I read it for a second time. Similar to the previous comment, there isn&#8217;t a lot I can add to what&#8217;s been said already, except to let you know how much I always have and will continue to appreciate your words and amazing talent for writing them in such a graceful way. I have always been inspired by your recipes and connection with food, but now feel totally and completely taken with your honestly, self-reflection, and bravery. My hope for you is peace, courage, love, and clarity as your continue through this new season in your life.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60040' data-commentid="60040" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60040" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Leslie" aria-label='Reply to Leslie'>Reply</a>    </div>
