    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Kayla</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60046"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-08T14:39:43-05:00">Thursday, December 8, 2016 at 2:39 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have read this most days since you posted it, and have sat crying big, fat, hard, happy tears every time.  As a woman who only ever dated men until I began coming out as queer a little over a year ago, I am deeply moved to hear someone speaking truth to the same things that I have, in some small way, also been experiencing.  It is even more profound to hear them in a voice that rings as clear as yours.  So: thank you.<br />
Have you read Mary Oliver&#8217;s Wild Geese (<a href="http://www.phys.unm.edu/~tw/fas/yits/archive/oliver_wildgeese.html" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.phys.unm.edu/~tw/fas/yits/archive/oliver_wildgeese.html</a>)?  You may have &#8211; it&#8217;s something of a favorite among the newly-queer, and it has held true for me time and time again when I feel myself faltering.   Wishing you joy to go with every sorrow, and the strength of family (in whatever form &#8220;family&#8221; takes for you).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60046' data-commentid="60046" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60046" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kayla" aria-label='Reply to Kayla'>Reply</a>    </div>
