    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly,</p>
<p>I discovered your blog and books this summer. You&#8217;re now one of my favorite writers and people who fall into the, &#8220;I have never met you, but you inspire me so and I hope to become as interesting as you one day&#8221; bucket). Your books also sit proudly with my cookbooks, though I think of them as falling into their own, different and special category that cannot be defined simply by the label &#8220;food memoir.&#8221; Labels can be so limiting. </p>
<p>Like so many of the folks here, I was so pleased to see a new blog post! I was eagerly anticipating a new recipe at the end of another excellent mini-read, but, have literally stopped in my tracks emotionally. I&#8217;m so sorry to hear about your marriage to Brandon, but, I am happy that you are finding love and support along this new journey. (And, I hope you are writing down literally everything that June says, ever). </p>
<p>You continue to inspire me as a writer, culinary maven, and great person. I&#8217;m looking forward to what comes next for you. It will be amazing. </p>
<p>Sincerely,<br />
Dana (current Portlander, former Ballardite, and loyal follower of all the things)</p>
    </div>

