  <li id="comment-60068" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Sandra</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60068"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-08T22:53:20-05:00">Thursday, December 8, 2016 at 10:53 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly,<br />
I was sent here by your most recent post.  My heart stopped when I read that you and Brandon are separating.  Oh, I can&#8217;t express how sad that makes me as I&#8217;ve read along with your story, all that you&#8217;ve shared, for many, many years.  How difficult, how searing, this must be for both of you.  Nothing is easy about change and something so seismic must be so hard for both of you.  </p>
<p>I think I can say all that and say with the same amount of truth: you can&#8217;t change who you are, no matter what.  You are who you are and if your writing is anything to go by, and it is, you are kind and sensitive and loving and would have never wished to go through the fire that you are experiencing.  Jesus, life can be so hard, can&#8217;t it?  Stand tall and proud.</p>
<p>I wish only the very best for you, Brandon and June.  You many not be married much longer, but you will always be family.  Find your tribe, support your daughter, and keep Brandon close.  It will all work out in the end &#8212; I know that from experience of having a divorce.  It may not look like you think it will, but it will all work out in the end.</p>
<p>Sorry this is so long as your writing makes us all feel as if we know you, although we don&#8217;t.  Best of luck to you and thank you for trusting us with your truth.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60068' data-commentid="60068" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60068" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sandra" aria-label='Reply to Sandra'>Reply</a>    </div>
