    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Jenna</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60071"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-09T01:14:04-05:00">Friday, December 9, 2016 at 1:14 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Dear Molly,<br />
A dear friend gave me A Homemade Life when I was in the hospital after the birth of my first child. In a country far from my entire family, I was terrified and disoriented, hospitalized days after a beautiful uncomplicated home birth, everything I had planned for and expected in my first week of motherhood was turned upside down. One particular night, I had gotten my only dose of painkillers since the birth and I felt on top of the world. My husband and newborn asleep in the bed, against all better judgement, I stayed up for hours that night relishing in my feeling OK for a few moments and started reading your book.<br />
I cherish your voice and have followed you ever since. I bless you to continue to be protected by your words themselves, this beautiful community you&#8217;ve built, and your family and friends. Thank you for your honesty, your bravery, and your you-ness. I am honored to be a witness.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
