    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">DVS</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60076"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-09T06:08:28-05:00">Friday, December 9, 2016 at 6:08 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I too have never commented but am a longtime off-and-on reader.  I left my husband of 16 years and am now married to my beautiful wife.  Our children are teenagers now.  They are happy and healthy.  As is their father.  And his wife and their new son.  As I contemplated over and over again if I was doing the right thing, I just kept asking myself what I would want my beautiful children to do in the same circumstance.  If I would want them to stay where they were unhappy.  Or not as happy as they could be.   Or not as true to who they are as they possibly could be.  And the answer was very very clear when that was the question.  Their father and I still parent them together. And now we do it with two additional wonderful women who have added to their lives in ways we are all very grateful for.  Everything will be amazing, Molly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60076' data-commentid="60076" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60076" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to DVS" aria-label='Reply to DVS'>Reply</a>    </div>
