    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I just spent the last hour crying, your writing and the responses by your readers touched me deeply. I am glad you felt like you were in a position to share this with us, and I can only imagine how the last couple of months have been for all of you. It is so &#8230; hard to admit that something isn&#8217;t working or rather, isn&#8217;t working anymore. Change happens whether you want it or not. But even harder is to communicate that insight to others, and then follow up on it by changing your life and that of others connected to you.  Congratulations to you, and respect to you and Brandon for how kindly you seem to be treating each other in these tumultuous times.</p>
