    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly,</p>
<p>I have loved your blog for several years and read both of your books this year. Spilled milk became the soundtrack to nine months of driving back and forth between home and my childhood home to take care of my dad, who was dying. Your chapter about your dad&#8217;s death in a homemade life was one of the most cathartic, brave, and beautiful things I read during that experience. Spilled milk made me smile during those long drives and your beautiful writing made me thoughtful and tearful.</p>
<p>Over the last I don&#8217;t know how long, while listening to spilled milk, I&#8217;ve heard what I thought were hints that you might be attracted to women (most recently, your interest in galadriel :)) . I figured I must be imagining things. I wasn&#8217;t surprised when I read this post and I am so happy for you despite the pain this change means. I hope you&#8217;ll share this experience with us and write with your usual candor, depth and wit. </p>
<p>Keep your chin up! And here are some books you might like:<br />
Euphoria<br />
Love, death and the changing of the seasons<br />
The price of salt<br />
Honey in the hive<br />
The education of Harriet hayfield<br />
Kinds of love</p>
    </div>

