    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I cannot fully express my gratitude to you for sharing this with all of us. I have been with you since one day when I was meandering through a book store and judged one by it&#8217;s cover and devoured it in a day and a half and was so glad I did. It led me to your blog and to realizing I didn&#8217;t always have to take food so seriously and to realizing I didn&#8217;t always have to take myself so seriously.<br />
I was with my daughter at her Waldorf School Advent Spiral the other night, where each child walks the dark path of greenery to the center with a candle, lights it, and then places it along the inside and walks out, and when the last of the children has put their candle down the entire spiral is illuminated. You can see.<br />
It&#8217;s a clear metaphor for the season, literally going in to the darkest times, and then bit by bit, little by little, the light grows. To me though, it also represented a renewal of spirit, maybe even being able to see a whole new sense of ourselves. This post made me think of that, and your beautiful writing and gut wrenching honesty and ability to live your truth has made me know that you are going to be just fine. May the days get lighter. xo</p>
    </div>

