  <li id="comment-60603" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Rebekah</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60603"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-31T00:36:20-05:00">Saturday, December 31, 2016 at 12:36 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi, Molly! I&#8217;m a huge fan of your writing and love that you are drawn to write about what&#8217;s real. I think that&#8217;s what we&#8217;re supposed to do as writers. It helps others make sense of their own journeys and feel less alone. Thank you for your honesty and bravery. </p>
<p>I came across this quote from Brené Brown and thought of you, “People may call what happens at midlife ‘a crisis’ but it’s not. It’s an unraveling — a time when you feel a desperate pull to live the life you want to live, not the one you’re ‘supposed’ to live. The unraveling is a time when you are challenged by the universe to let go of who you think you are supposed to be and to embrace who you are.” </p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60603' data-commentid="60603" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60603" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Rebekah" aria-label='Reply to Rebekah'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-60617" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Wendy</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60617"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-12-31T18:05:44-05:00">Saturday, December 31, 2016 at 6:05 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, this is one of the most brave things I think a person can do. To be honest with yourself, in spite of the absolute mess that follows the honesty. I think about all of the people who were and will never be that brave (understandably), and I imagine them cheering for you. You have chosen to take the difficult path, a path I imagine will eventually turn into the easier path, but with no crystal ball it must at times feel like your chest is collapsing. I applaud you for choosing to live your life and choosing the hope for true happiness over the certainty of the status quo. I&#8217;m sure you know you will face difficult times ahead, but my hope for you is that when you are old and grey, you will be proud of yourself and know above all else that your honesty freed you and so many others in your life.<br />
Hugs</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60617' data-commentid="60617" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60617" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Wendy" aria-label='Reply to Wendy'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-60622" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Ellen</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-60622"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2017-01-01T02:18:50-05:00">Sunday, January 1, 2017 at 2:18 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I have been a lurker on your blog for years, like before-Delancey years.  I have loved your words, used your recipes, and enjoyed your recommendations.  I check in with your blog every couple of months, and so I am late to this party.  Nonetheless, I wanted to break my silence for this post:  I cannot imagine how hard it must have been to figure this out, then tell the people in your life, and then tell us.  And I am grateful to see this example of honest living.  I admire you for demanding to live your life authentically.  I wish you happiness and joy in seeking/finding new loves to add to those already in your life.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-60622' data-commentid="60622" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-60622" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Ellen" aria-label='Reply to Ellen'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
