    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Wow &#8211; that brought a lot of tears welling to the surface.  First of all, thank you for sharing this.  I&#8217;ve followed you since the beginning, have eaten at your restaurants, purchased your books, but I&#8217;ve never commented, never spoken up, even when I knew it was you at your restaurant.  I think I just didn&#8217;t want to be THAT fan. LOL.  But this post &#8230; sigh&#8230; like other commenters have said &#8211; you are like a close friend who&#8217;s spilling her heart out.  At the very least, I wanted to share a hug.  But I also wanted to say that it&#8217;s always been your courage that I find so striking.  Sure &#8211; life in all it&#8217;s jumbled up mess makes it challenging to move forward and push past our fears &#8211; but you?  You keep doing it.  You might be kicking and screaming and gritting your teeth about it &#8211; lol &#8211; but you keep pushing ahead.  May not mean much coming from a stranger &#8211; but I&#8217;ll say it anyway&#8230;. I&#8217;m proud of you.  Keep on being you Mama!  You help us all be a little bit braver.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
