    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly,</p>
<p>That was so beautifully written and so strikingly honest.  Thank you for sharing your heart and here&#8217;s a little bit of mine in solidarity&#8230;When I first met you I was so intimidated.  I&#8217;m pretty shy but it was more about, &#8220;wow this amazing human is my boyfriend&#8217;s boss&#8230;&#8221;  She&#8217;s so wise and cool and what can I even say to her.  (I really need to work on my confidence around inspiring people).   So I stood back and always just admired you and Brandon quietly from afar.  You guys were a couple that Cody and I looked up to for years, how could we not?  You guys are great entepreners and creatives, you can really break it down on the dance floor, and kill at karaoke, you have the coolest daughter, and everyone loves and adores you.  These are all life goals that I have for Cody and I.  So when I heard about your separation, which was right around the time we decided to get married, it made me sad and worried about my own future marriage.  But over this past year you both have rewritten what a separation can be and what real love and respect are.  Maintaining the respect you and Brandon share for each other is honorary.  Your story, your bravery, and your dedication to following your heart is all so inspiring.  Thank you for sharing your experience, I&#8217;ll reflect on this for guidance, comfort, and hope when I hit my own rough roads.  Keep searching and keep loving.</p>
    </div>

