    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly &#8211; I am somehow just reading this today. Perhaps because I needed to read it now. Just before Christmas, I lost my only sister and have been struggling with how life goes on without her. Your ability to articulate so beautifully your own very personal life changes have given me the courage to address my own weaknesses, and begin a new year with honesty and kindness. The truth is, we have to be truthful no matter how hard it may be. We each have our own very personal &#8220;truths&#8221;.  As our lives grow and evolve, so do we. It never stops. That is the only thing that I know for certain. I wish you and Brandon all that you need to continue to be a family in whatever way that works for the three of you. Your courage gives each of us a piece of your strength. For that I thank you eternally. xo</p>
