  <li id="comment-61587" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Laura</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-61587"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2017-01-26T11:51:19-05:00">Thursday, January 26, 2017 at 11:51 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I haven&#8217;t checked out your blog in some time. It is brave and wonderful for you to tell your story. I too discovered my orientation changing as an adult (32). It was scary and exciting and organic. We have to let go of who we think we should be and embrace who we are, who we will become. Sending much love to you, Brandon and June as you move forward together.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-61587' data-commentid="61587" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-61587" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Laura" aria-label='Reply to Laura'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-61643" class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Jess</cite></div>
      <a href="http://orangette.net/2016/11/november-30/#comment-61643"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2017-01-28T17:59:31-05:00">Saturday, January 28, 2017 at 5:59 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly. Number one, your writing is incredible. Number two, wow. And thank you.<br />
I am an old reader, someone who followed you closely, about 8 years ago. I made a certain cake recipe of yours all the time, whipped it up without the recipe every time grinds came by because I knew it by heart. Then somehow my life took over, I stopped following food blogs, stopped writing, became consumed by my babies and my own post-partum depression, and eventually my divorce as well. Now I&#8217;m through all of that and out on the other side, literally out! Finallu came out to my mom, thankfully not at 2am in an emergency room, and it&#8217;s been a good ol&#8217; weird time ever since.<br />
Today for some odd reason I suddenly remembered your blog, hurriedly sought you out, and read this. I am astounded by the beauty in your words, by your strong wise spirit, and by how similar our stories sound- minus the restaurant on my end, though I did have a good business for a short time.<br />
Thank you for sharing your story. Thank you so much.<br />
In solidarity,<br />
Jess</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
