    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Change strikes just when you think you have it all settled, right?<br />
I understand 100% the challenge and effort you and Brandon are making for June.  My son&#8217;s father and I split up when my son was 4 (now 10).  My ex is a wonderful person and an amazing father, but we were incredibly unhappy together.  We initially focused on creating the best possible experience for our son and that helped us through the toughest times.<br />
Even with a great relationship as exes and co-parents, it can still be challenging to negotiate changes later in life.  There were times I sickeningly realized that by leaving I had given up my right to influence my ex-partner&#8217;s friends, family, and actions.  How would I feel about a new girlfriend, wife, sibling, etc??  Thankfully, my ex and I both found wonderful new companions who have similarly wonderful relationships with our son.<br />
Parenting is a challenge together or separate or separately together, but you have done your entire family a great service by being true to yourself.  Keep up the good work!</p>
    </div>

