    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Thank you. I haven&#8217;t checked in in a while either. Because I was afraid to read the &#8220;big news, I&#8217;m pregnant/ had a secret baby&#8221; post. My husband and I separated officially November and our little guy will be four at the end of May. Much like you  (and so many of your readers!) we&#8217;re co parenting (and still living together&#8230;.) and feel like our new objective is to have the best divorce known to man! It feels that way when we go bowling together and cheer like crazy people when Archie got his first strike. Other days, it&#8217;s a cry- on- the bathroom-floor  and just so hard. And sad. And part of the loss and grief I feel is the question of more children. Will I? Will my son know the love/hate perfection of siblings? I don&#8217;t know. I feel like I don&#8217;t know much these days. Like you, I hate change, I love being able to look and plan ahead. My life has a different filter now, and maybe that&#8217;s the lesson I need to take.</p>
    </div>

