    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly &#8212;<br />
I can feel the weight and courage of your words in my chest, heavy and strong. In part, this is because my marriage dissolved right around the same time yours did, and my daughter, who is four, asks very similar questions. Thank you for telling the truth, which is the hardest and most important thing. From far off, in my own little corner of the writing/cooking/parenting/heartbreak world, I am in your corner. May life and love buoy you as you and your loves navigate this strange water. You are strong enough (and I know that as I say it to you, I also say it to me.)</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-67230' data-commentid="67230" data-postid="9748" data-belowelement="comment-67230" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Erinn" aria-label='Reply to Erinn'>Reply</a>    </div>
